    • Method Detail

      • isDocumentDataMatch

        boolean isDocumentDataMatch()
        Returns true if data from scanned parts/sides of the document match, false otherwise. For example if date of expiry is scanned from the front and back side of the document and values do not match, this method will return false. Result will be only if scanned values for all fields that are compared are the same.
        Returns:
        true if data from scanned parts/sides of the document match, false otherwise.
